so it doesnt contain any html tags
ChatGPT said:
Correct! When the web tool provides raw data, it generally doesn't include HTML tags directly in the response. Instead, it returns structured data in a format such as JSON or a similar structure, which is much cleaner and easier to work with programmatically.

To clarify:

Search engines like Google or APIs (such as Bing or a custom search engine) return data in structured formats like JSON or XML that contain the relevant details such as titles, URLs, snippets, etc. These responses don’t include HTML tags as you would find in the body of a webpage.

Parsing the Data: The tool extracts information from the raw search result, such as:

Title
Snippet (summary or preview text)
Image URL (if available)
Source (name of the publication)
Publication Date (if available)
